node.text: This is Wings of Rescue. Our sponsor, @titosvodka, will match up to $20,000 in donations sent their way through the link in our bio. Wings of Rescue flies dogs like Clyde from overcrowded shelters and disaster areas to shelters with empty kennel space where they’ll be adopted in no time. They’ve saved 8,597 pets this year already and can save way more with your help. Everyone involved gets a 14/10 from us [EDIT: initial goal of $20k hit in 45 minutes, secondary goal of $40k hit in 3 1/2 hours]

node.text: This is Scrappy Doo. He knows he peed right before the road trip started, but he has to again. Cannot help that he is a hydrated king. 14/10 (follow @blaine.myers.3990)

node.text: This is Chloe. She was hit by a car, but has been telling everyone she got into a bar fight with a mailman. Regardless, we’ve paid her remaining medical bills. Please consider getting pet medical insurance. It’s best to be puppared. 13/10 would sign her cast

node.text: This is Toby. He just had emergency surgery to remove a softball-sized tumor that ruptured his kidney. It was successful and thankfully it wasn’t cancerous. He still has some time until he’s fully recovered, but his family is so grateful he’ll be around to show his little brother the ropes. You can help Toby with his medical bills by clicking the link in our bio. 13/10 [EDIT: fully funded in 82 minutes]

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by WeRateDogs® on July 15, 2021 tagging @justfoodfordogs, and @keiko.and.niko. May be an image of 1 person, dog and indoor.

node.text:
This is Niko and his very supportive brother, Keiko. Niko has solar dermatitis. If he’s exposed to the sun, he can develop a rash. To keep him safe, he wears custom pajamas, which he doesn’t mind because he looks so h*ckin handsome in them. 

To get the allergies under control, his human went looking for a diet that would provide all the nutrients Niko’s body would need to fight off the solar dermatitis flares. That’s when she discovered @justfoodfordogs. 

After just six weeks on their new diet, Niko showed fewer signs of rash irritation from all his allergies. It was clear his quality of life had improved dramatically with the switch. He can now get back to more important things, like cuddling as close as he possibly can to Keiko. 14/10 for both
@justfoodfordogs #partner
(thank you @keiko.and.niko for sharing your story with us)

May be an image of dog and text that says 'LCC K-9 Comfort Dogs @K9ComfortDogs The LCC K-9 Comfort Dogs are on their way to #Surfside. Please pray for everyone impacted by the tragedy. TOBIAS Please PetMe Pet TOBIAS LLBean'.

node.text:
This is Tobias. He and his comfort dog friends have been in Surfside, Florida all week. They brought their “please pet me” vests and all the love they could fit in their backpacks. They also handed out mini stuffed comfort dogs, so first responders and families who lost loved ones can continue to receive a “golden retriever hug” as often as they need it. 15/10 for all

@comfortdogs only go where they are invited and never charge those they serve. Unfortunately, you’ve probably seen their incredible work before. If you’d like to support their efforts or purchase your own mini stuffed comfort dog, please visit the link in our bio

node.text:
This is Midge and Rowan. They think they’re the same size, and comfort each other with both kisses and cuddles. For anything those can’t fix, they have @Trupanion

“Trupanion allows owners to pursue surgery or aggressive care for their beloved furry friend when they may otherwise not have been able to. I can sleep at night knowing I’ll be all set if anything happens to my little scruffy girl, Midge, because Trupanion has my back.” 13/10 #partner (thank you @lovemidgexoxo for sharing your Trupanion Tail with us)

node.text: This is Chewie. She is 16 years old, and paraplegic due to a neurological deficit. Her favorite thing to do is float. Her second favorite thing to do is take a nap while she floats. 14/10 #SeniorPupSaturday
